It is needless to complain of the crabbed writing‚ which for illegibility surpasses anything Ι had yet seen, and equals anything I have seen since, even amongst the worst of the Prague MSS. This is a diffi- culty which all transcribers of Wyclif will by this time have learned to take as a matter of course. And yet it is but fair to point out that in difficult passages, such as abound in Logiccz from beginning to end, this very greatly increases the perplexity of the editor. More than once —— and I might say, more than fifty times —I have been obliged to note down the abbreviations of the MS. with the unuttered reservation: Unless the sign stands for something quite different! A reservation that is by no means unjustifiable.
